  description: |||
    Height of the top of canopy above bare earth (Canopy Height Model; CHM);
    data are mosaicked over the AOP footprint onto a spatially uniform grid at 1
    m spatial resolution. The CHM is generated by creating a continuous surface
    of canopy height estimates across the entire spatial domain of the LiDAR
    survey, derived from the LiDAR point cloud. The point cloud is separated
    into classes representing the ground and vegetation returns.  The ground
    classified points allow for calculation of a height normalized point cloud
    to provide a relative estimate of vegetation elevation. A surface is then
    generated using the height normalized vegetation points to produce the
    CHM. Any canopy heights less than 2m are set to zero for data collected with
    the Optech Gemini LiDAR sensors, and less than 2/3m for the Riegl and Optech
    Galaxy sensors.

    See [NEON Data Product DP3.30015.001](
    https://data.neonscience.org/data-products/DP3.30015.001) for
    more details.

